
Petersburg, 18 Jan. 1781. Last August Elliott purchased, at Gen. Muhlenbergs request, a quantity of saddles and bridles from Josiah Moffitt which cost 22,945, paying 2,000 from money on hand. The Council has refused payment of the balance for want of a printed certificate. Although instructed not to issue certificates after a date which was prior to the purchase, encloses one, which, if proper, should be given to Mr. Moffitt, who has renderd a singular Service; it is a Great Pitty he Should Suffer or be Discouragd.
